name: lib/Request.js
lib/Response.js
send
description: Writes the output data and calls `http.ServerResponse#end()`

name: write
description:
Calls and returns the result of `http.ServerResponse#write(this.body)`
and resets `this.body` back to an empty string.

name: lib/env.js
env
description:
If only the `name` parameter is provided this function acts as a getter for
`process.env`. However if `name` and `value` are provide it acts as a setter
for `process.env`. When acting as a getter the function will try to call
`JSON.parse()` on the value cast to lowercase _(to convert `'true'` to `true`,
`'TRUE'` to `true`, `'1'` to `1`, etc.)_ and if that fails it will return the
value verbatim.

params.name: name
params.description: The envvar name to interact with.

params.name: value
params.description: If provided sets the value of the `name` envvar.

return.description: The parsed envvar value, regardless of if called as a getter or setter.

name: lib/index.js
route
description:
A helper method to work with the instance's internal `#routes` property.
Acts as a getter if the `route` parameter is not specified and a setter
if it is. This method always returns the specified route object.

params.name: path
params.description: The path name to get/set the route _(e.g. `'/resource'`)_.

params.name: route
params.description: An object consisting of callback functions mapped to method keys.

params.name: settings
params.description: The port setting defaults to the value of the `BQ_RUN_DEFAULT_PORT` envvar.

return.description: The server instance that has been started.

name: serve
description: The callback invoked by `#run()` when the server receives a client request.
